@startuml
'title High Level Architecture - Playwright Automated Tests

left to right direction
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

' ==============================
' Solution
' ==============================

package "PolyglotPlatform Solution" {

    component "PolyglotPlatform.AutomatedTests\n(.NET Test Project)" as TESTS
    component "SmokeTests.cs\nNUnit Test Class\n(PageTest base class)" as SMOKE
    file "playwright.runsettings\n(manually added)" as RUNSETTINGS
}

component "Visual Studio Test Explorer" as VS
component "Microsoft Edge " as EDGE

' ==============================
' Project Structure
' ==============================

TESTS --> SMOKE : contains tests
TESTS --> RUNSETTINGS : reads configuration

VS --> TESTS : run tests

' ==============================
' NuGet Packages
' ==============================

component "Microsoft.Playwright.NUnit\n1.58.0\n<<NuGet>>" as PW_NUNIT
component "NUnit\n3.14.0\n<<NuGet>>" as NUNIT
component "NUnit3TestAdapter\n4.5.0\n<<NuGet>>" as ADAPTER
component "Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk\n17.8.0\n<<NuGet>>" as TESTSDK
component "NUnit.Analyzers\n3.9.0\n<<NuGet>>" as ANALYZERS
component "coverlet.collector\n6.0.0\n<<NuGet>>" as COVERLET

TESTS ..> PW_NUNIT : uses
TESTS ..> NUNIT : uses
TESTS ..> ADAPTER : test discovery
TESTS ..> TESTSDK : test runtime
TESTS ..> ANALYZERS : code analysis
TESTS ..> COVERLET : code coverage

PW_NUNIT --> EDGE : launches browser

' ==============================
' Notes
' ==============================

note right of RUNSETTINGS
Added manually to the solution.

Configured in Visual Studio:

Test -> Configure Run Settings
-> Select Solution Wide runsettings File
-> playwright.runsettings

Purpose:
- Force Playwright to use Edge
- Prevent Playwright from downloading browsers
- Suitable for corporate laptops
end note

note right of SMOKE
Playwright test class.

public class SmokeTests : PageTest

Contains Playwright tests.
end note

note bottom of EDGE
RunSettings configuration:

BrowserName = chromium
Channel = msedge
Headless = false
end note

@enduml